1
00:00:38,640 --> 00:00:40,040
I can't...

2
00:00:40,120 --> 00:00:41,760
(MUTTERING)

3
00:00:43,240 --> 00:00:45,120
It should be there. Hmm.

4
00:00:47,280 --> 00:00:49,280
What? Oh.

5
00:00:50,320 --> 00:00:52,840
Well... Well, this must be it.

6
00:00:57,360 --> 00:00:58,560
(SIGHS)

7
00:01:00,520 --> 00:01:01,920
Is there anything on my head?

8
00:01:02,640 --> 00:01:03,920
Uh... Well, yes.

9
00:01:04,000 --> 00:01:06,480
-Describe it.
-Well, you've sort of got antlers.

10
00:01:06,640 --> 00:01:08,200
-Antlers?
-Yes. Antlers.

11
00:01:09,320 --> 00:01:10,720
-Antlers!
-Mmm.

12
00:01:11,800 --> 00:01:14,560
You are a time-space machine.

13
00:01:14,640 --> 00:01:17,120
You're a vehicle.
I have never asked you to cheer me up

14
00:01:17,200 --> 00:01:19,560
with hologramatic antlers!

15
00:01:19,640 --> 00:01:21,640
-(TARDIS BEEPING)
-Thank you.

16
00:01:23,560 --> 00:01:25,320
-Can I help you?
-Yes, are you the surgeon?

17
00:01:25,400 --> 00:01:26,840
-Close enough. Why?
-Well, you know.

18
00:01:26,920 --> 00:01:29,160
-I don't know.
-There's a medical emergency.

19
00:01:29,600 --> 00:01:31,400
Will there be singing?

20
00:01:32,240 --> 00:01:33,480
No.

21
00:01:33,560 --> 00:01:34,840
Fine, then.

22
00:01:34,960 --> 00:01:36,800
NARDOLE: We weren't sure
where you'd come down.

23
00:01:36,880 --> 00:01:38,760
DOCTOR: Sorry?
NARDOLE: In your capsule.

24
00:01:38,840 --> 00:01:41,840
Oh, I'm never sure.
I don't like being sure about things.

25
00:01:41,920 --> 00:01:43,920
One minute you're sure, the next
everybody turns into lizards

26
00:01:44,000 --> 00:01:45,400
and a piano falls on you.

27
00:01:45,520 --> 00:01:48,160
-Piano?
-It's been a long day.

28
00:01:50,520 --> 00:01:52,480
Are you expecting a surgeon?

29
00:01:53,000 --> 00:01:54,720
DOCTOR: So what's the medical emergency?

30
00:01:54,800 --> 00:01:56,320
NARDOLE: Didn't you read the agreement?

31
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,640
There it is.

32
00:02:00,480 --> 00:02:02,920
DOCTOR: What?
NARDOLE: There, that's it.

33
00:02:03,440 --> 00:02:04,920
That's what?

34
00:02:06,000 --> 00:02:07,480
Oh, the flying saucer.

35
00:02:08,120 --> 00:02:09,280
Is that new?

36
00:02:18,200 --> 00:02:19,400
Come on.

37
00:02:20,720 --> 00:02:22,120
WOMAN: Well, you took your time.

38
00:02:22,360 --> 00:02:23,560
Sorry, ma'am.

39
00:02:23,800 --> 00:02:26,120
This is him. This is the surgeon.

40
00:02:26,200 --> 00:02:28,600
-Hello.
-You don't look much like your pictures.

41
00:02:28,720 --> 00:02:31,520
-Well, that's an ongoing problem for me.
-Doesn't look very impressive, does he?

42
00:02:31,600 --> 00:02:33,520
Nardole, what have you brought
to my doorstep?

43
00:02:33,600 --> 00:02:35,240
I've had a haircut.
This is my best suit.

44
00:02:35,320 --> 00:02:36,560
It's not even a suit.

45
00:02:38,360 --> 00:02:40,640
-Do I know you?
-You most certainly do not.

46
00:02:41,960 --> 00:02:43,400
And now that you've met me,

47
00:02:43,480 --> 00:02:45,240
you'll do your very best to forget me.

48
00:02:45,320 --> 00:02:47,560
-River!
-Oi!

49
00:02:47,640 --> 00:02:49,440
Dr Song to you.

50
00:02:49,920 --> 00:02:51,880
Sometimes Professor but mainly Doctor.

51
00:02:52,320 --> 00:02:54,120
RIVER: Don't use my name, ever!

52
00:02:55,360 --> 00:02:56,520
How do you know me?

53
00:02:56,600 --> 00:02:58,040
Well, it's a tiny bit complicated.

54
00:02:58,120 --> 00:02:59,760
People usually need a flow chart.

55
00:02:59,840 --> 00:03:01,640
RIVER: It doesn't matter.

56
00:03:01,720 --> 00:03:03,640
If either of you use my name again,

57
00:03:03,800 --> 00:03:06,360
I will remove your organs
in alphabetical order.

58
00:03:06,720 --> 00:03:08,480
-Any questions?
-Which alphabet?

59
00:03:10,000 --> 00:03:12,080
Sorry, you really didn't want
these questions, did you?

60
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:14,560
This way. We don't have a lot of time.

61
00:03:15,920 --> 00:03:18,040
-What seems to be the problem?
-My husband.

62
00:03:18,880 --> 00:03:20,080
Your husband?

63
00:03:20,200 --> 00:03:22,480
Didn't you read my message?
My husband, yes.

64
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:24,520
My husband is dying.

65
00:03:27,960 --> 00:03:29,280
Something wrong?

66
00:03:31,400 --> 00:03:33,320
I think I'm going to need
a bigger flow chart.

67
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:37,480
(DOCTOR WHO THEME)

68
00:04:13,840 --> 00:04:15,240
(MONKS CHANTING)

69
00:04:20,680 --> 00:04:22,720
Husband, I return to you.

70
00:04:23,720 --> 00:04:25,000
HYDROFLAX: Where is my queen?

71
00:04:25,840 --> 00:04:27,880
Never far from you, my love.

72
00:04:28,520 --> 00:04:30,320
(GRUNTING)

73
00:04:30,920 --> 00:04:32,240
DOCTOR: No, wait.

74
00:04:34,360 --> 00:04:36,560
-That's your husband?
-Listen,

75
00:04:36,640 --> 00:04:38,480
you are being watched
by four billion people.

76
00:04:38,560 --> 00:04:41,360
You are surrounded by warrior monks
with sentient laser swords,

77
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:44,440
genetically engineered anger problems
and not enough to do.

78
00:04:44,520 --> 00:04:47,040
Best to stay still
and keep your hands by your sides.

79
00:04:47,120 --> 00:04:49,200
No, wait. (STAMMERING)

80
00:04:49,400 --> 00:04:51,280
-That's your husband?
-My husband,

81
00:04:51,360 --> 00:04:53,640
your patient. King Hydroflax.

82
00:04:53,960 --> 00:04:56,240
Yes. That's who
you're married to? Not...

83
00:04:56,400 --> 00:04:58,200
-anybody else?
-HYDROFLAX: My love.

84
00:04:58,480 --> 00:04:59,960
Attend me, woman.

85
00:05:00,040 --> 00:05:01,400
RIVER: I fly to you.

86
00:05:01,960 --> 00:05:03,960
-Is there a problem?
-Right, so you don't recognise me, then?

87
00:05:04,040 --> 00:05:05,360
Why would I recognise you?

88
00:05:05,440 --> 00:05:06,560
Oh, no reason.

89
00:05:09,720 --> 00:05:12,280
I don't like him. You like him?

90
00:05:12,880 --> 00:05:14,080
Don't cross your arms.

91
00:05:14,160 --> 00:05:16,800
He's a lying-down person.
I don't like lying-down people.

92
00:05:16,880 --> 00:05:18,000
It's so untidy.

93
00:05:18,080 --> 00:05:20,280
Keep your arms by your side,
like she said.

94
00:05:20,360 --> 00:05:22,080
RIVER: My one true love,

95
00:05:22,440 --> 00:05:25,160
the only husband I will ever have.

96
00:05:25,240 --> 00:05:28,120
My time with you has been too short.

97
00:05:28,200 --> 00:05:31,320
You have given me days of adventure

98
00:05:32,160 --> 00:05:35,000
-and many nights of passion.
-Oh...

99
00:05:35,520 --> 00:05:36,680
Why do you keep crossing them?

100
00:05:36,760 --> 00:05:38,040
Because they're cross.
I've got cross arms.

101
00:05:38,120 --> 00:05:39,320
HYDROFLAX: The end is near.

102
00:05:39,600 --> 00:05:40,760
I feel it.

103
00:05:40,840 --> 00:05:42,360
RIVER: Oh, forgive me, my lord.

104
00:05:42,600 --> 00:05:44,680
I have acted against your instructions.

105
00:05:44,760 --> 00:05:45,800
My love?

106
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:47,280
RIVER: If you die this day,

107
00:05:47,360 --> 00:05:50,520
this galaxy will drown in tears.

108
00:05:50,960 --> 00:05:53,360
Look at them. Your people.

109
00:05:53,440 --> 00:05:56,160
They watch and hope and pray.

110
00:05:56,560 --> 00:05:59,320
With so much at stake,
I followed my heart.

111
00:05:59,400 --> 00:06:01,480
I disobeyed your orders

112
00:06:02,040 --> 00:06:07,960
and sent for the finest surgeon
in the galaxy!

113
00:06:08,160 --> 00:06:10,440
(CROWD CHEERING ON TV SCREENS)

114
00:06:20,560 --> 00:06:22,280
(CHUCKLING)

115
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:28,360
This might be an alarming question
in the circumstance

116
00:06:28,720 --> 00:06:31,320
but you really do think I'm a surgeon,
don't you?

117
00:06:32,640 --> 00:06:33,920
Oh...

118
00:06:34,040 --> 00:06:36,040
(SOFTLY) Okay, calm down.
Keep it together.

119
00:06:36,120 --> 00:06:37,160
Don't make puddles.

120
00:06:37,400 --> 00:06:38,400
RIVER: Surgeon.

121
00:06:38,840 --> 00:06:40,960
-Attend your patient.
-(NARDOLE WHIMPERING)

122
00:06:49,240 --> 00:06:50,920
Any tiny hint of
what species he might be?

123
00:06:51,000 --> 00:06:52,120
(WHIMPERING) I don't know.

124
00:06:52,240 --> 00:06:54,000
Okay, never mind, you just stay there.

125
00:06:54,440 --> 00:06:56,520
You're probably going to need a mop.

126
00:06:59,360 --> 00:07:00,640
Bow.

127
00:07:00,720 --> 00:07:01,840
Sorry, what?

128
00:07:01,920 --> 00:07:04,480
You are in the presence
of His Infinite Majesty,

129
00:07:04,560 --> 00:07:06,280
King Hydroflax. You will bow.

130
00:07:06,440 --> 00:07:08,440
Oh, no, I'm sorry, Your Majesty.
I can't do that.

131
00:07:08,720 --> 00:07:09,840
-(NARDOLE WHIMPERS)
-You what?

132
00:07:09,920 --> 00:07:11,080
-It's my back.
-RIVER: Your back?

133
00:07:11,160 --> 00:07:12,760
Yeah, my back's playing up.

134
00:07:12,960 --> 00:07:15,400
It simply refuses to carry the weight

135
00:07:15,480 --> 00:07:17,960
of an entirely pointless
stratum of society

136
00:07:18,040 --> 00:07:20,400
who contribute nothing of worth
to the world

137
00:07:20,480 --> 00:07:23,320
and crush the hopes and dreams
of working people.

138
00:07:28,400 --> 00:07:30,680
Can you save me, surgeon?

139
00:07:30,800 --> 00:07:32,120
Well, that depends upon
what's wrong with you.

140
00:07:32,240 --> 00:07:34,560
-There's something in his brain.
-You could have fooled me.

141
00:07:34,680 --> 00:07:38,040
-(GRUNTING)
-Oh, oh, sorry. (LAUGHING)

142
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:41,960
Sorry. Just gallows humour.

143
00:07:42,280 --> 00:07:44,200
-Probably the wrong word.
-Yeah, I would say it is.

144
00:07:44,360 --> 00:07:46,600
My love, you must rest.

145
00:07:46,680 --> 00:07:49,760
The surgeon and I
will discuss the procedure.

146
00:07:50,080 --> 00:07:53,240
Prepare, master of my life,

147
00:07:53,920 --> 00:07:55,720
to live anew.

148
00:07:57,400 --> 00:07:59,200
Patience be with you all!

149
00:07:59,320 --> 00:08:02,600
Our king will rise again.

150
00:08:02,680 --> 00:08:05,400
ALL: Our king will rise again!

151
00:08:06,360 --> 00:08:09,320
CROWD: Our king will rise again!

152
00:08:10,240 --> 00:08:14,080
Hydroflax! Hydroflax!

153
00:08:14,160 --> 00:08:16,480
All right, enough of this. Joke's over.

154
00:08:16,560 --> 00:08:17,840
-What joke?
-Look at me.

155
00:08:17,920 --> 00:08:19,040
Why?

156
00:08:20,200 --> 00:08:22,000
-I'm the Doctor.
-(SCOFFS) You'd better be.

157
00:08:22,080 --> 00:08:23,880
You've got an operation to perform.

158
00:08:25,480 --> 00:08:29,200
Here's the entry wound,
just below the hairline, and...

159
00:08:30,320 --> 00:08:31,800
there's the projectile.

160
00:08:32,320 --> 00:08:34,360
Should've killed him straight off
but he's very strong.

161
00:08:34,560 --> 00:08:35,840
That's not a bullet.

162
00:08:35,920 --> 00:08:37,160
It's a diamond.

163
00:08:37,560 --> 00:08:39,560
-How'd it get in there?
-At speed.

164
00:08:40,080 --> 00:08:41,920
Do you recognise it?

165
00:08:43,440 --> 00:08:45,080
-No!
-Yes.

166
00:08:45,200 --> 00:08:47,360
-The Halassi Androvar?
-The very same.

167
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:49,760
Hydroflax was leading the raid
on the Halassi vaults.

168
00:08:49,880 --> 00:08:52,720
In the ensuing firefight,
the whole thing blew up in his face,

169
00:08:52,800 --> 00:08:56,960
with the result that he now has the
most valuable diamond in the universe

170
00:08:57,280 --> 00:09:01,600
lodged three inches
inside his enormous head.

171
00:09:02,240 --> 00:09:04,120
So,

172
00:09:05,480 --> 00:09:07,960
-can you remove it?
-It's very small.

173
00:09:08,480 --> 00:09:09,960
Might be difficult to manoeuvre it.

174
00:09:10,120 --> 00:09:11,800
Not the diamond.

175
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,120
His head.

176
00:09:15,240 --> 00:09:17,080
-His head?
-Yes.

177
00:09:17,360 --> 00:09:19,960
I think it would be easier just to
remove the whole thing, don't you?

178
00:09:20,040 --> 00:09:21,920
-But wouldn't that kill him?
-Well, you're the medical expert,

179
00:09:22,000 --> 00:09:23,760
but I'd say so, yes.

180
00:09:23,840 --> 00:09:25,040
-Your husband?
-Sort of.

181
00:09:25,120 --> 00:09:27,160
-"Sort of"?
-I basically married the diamond.

182
00:09:28,280 --> 00:09:30,000
The Halassi want their diamond back,

183
00:09:30,080 --> 00:09:32,000
-so they came to me.
-Why?

184
00:09:32,160 --> 00:09:33,480
I'm an archaeologist.

185
00:09:33,560 --> 00:09:35,000
Slash murderer, slash thief.

186
00:09:35,080 --> 00:09:38,880
An archaeologist is just a thief,
with patience.

187
00:09:38,960 --> 00:09:41,480
Never had much of that.
it'll fit in here, don't you think?

188
00:09:41,720 --> 00:09:43,040
I've checked it for leaks.

189
00:09:43,320 --> 00:09:44,520
Is this what you're like when I'm not...

190
00:09:44,600 --> 00:09:45,840
Not what?

191
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:48,360
-You're talking about murdering someone.
-No, I'm not.

192
00:09:48,600 --> 00:09:49,960
I'm actually murdering someone.

193
00:09:50,440 --> 00:09:51,920
Cheer up, get a saw.

194
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:54,160
I'll kill the lights,
you kill the patient.

195
00:09:54,640 --> 00:09:57,320
I employed you. You agreed to this.

196
00:09:57,400 --> 00:10:00,960
Do you not know who that man is?

197
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:04,160
King Hydroflax,
the Butcher of the Bone Meadows,

198
00:10:04,320 --> 00:10:07,280
who ends his battles
by eating his enemies,

199
00:10:07,360 --> 00:10:08,440
dead or alive!

200
00:10:08,520 --> 00:10:09,560
The murder of a creature like that

201
00:10:09,640 --> 00:10:11,240
wouldn't weigh very heavily
on my conscience,

202
00:10:11,320 --> 00:10:12,400
even if I had one.

203
00:10:13,800 --> 00:10:15,360
What's that face?

204
00:10:15,920 --> 00:10:18,080
Are you thinking?

205
00:10:18,360 --> 00:10:20,840
Stop it! You're a man. It looks weird.

206
00:10:20,960 --> 00:10:22,200
I need more information.

207
00:10:22,560 --> 00:10:24,200
-For what?
-For my diagnosis.

208
00:10:24,280 --> 00:10:27,720
He's dying, we're about to steal
his head and scoop out his brains.

209
00:10:27,800 --> 00:10:29,000
Aren't we over-thinking?

210
00:10:29,160 --> 00:10:32,040
I'll be the judge of that.
I'm the Doctor.

211
00:10:32,880 --> 00:10:34,760
You know who you remind me of?

212
00:10:34,880 --> 00:10:36,920
Yes. Probably a chap with a big...

213
00:10:37,120 --> 00:10:38,640
My second wife.

214
00:10:44,680 --> 00:10:46,600
(WARRIOR MONKS YELLING)

215
00:10:51,120 --> 00:10:52,840
Darling!

216
00:10:53,320 --> 00:10:54,720
You're up and about!

217
00:10:54,800 --> 00:10:57,280
-False wife.
-How much better you're looking.

218
00:10:57,480 --> 00:10:58,640
You planned to take my head.

219
00:10:58,840 --> 00:11:00,080
Never crossed my mind.

220
00:11:00,160 --> 00:11:03,240
-Is this your bag?
-Perhaps you should've just asked.

221
00:11:20,000 --> 00:11:21,280
RIVER: Well...

222
00:11:21,600 --> 00:11:24,400
I wondered why we didn't
share a bathroom.

223
00:11:24,560 --> 00:11:26,120
You married a cyborg
and didn't even know?

224
00:11:26,200 --> 00:11:29,240
I will have you flogged and flayed
and burned.

225
00:11:29,320 --> 00:11:33,040
I will crush every last remnant of you
from this universe.

226
00:11:33,160 --> 00:11:35,120
How dare you? I'm your wife!

227
00:11:35,240 --> 00:11:37,840
-You planned to murder me!
-Don't change the subject.

228
00:11:37,920 --> 00:11:40,560
Why are you doing this? Who are you?

229
00:11:41,000 --> 00:11:42,240
I'm Professor River Song.

230
00:11:42,360 --> 00:11:45,240
You have an ancient artefact
of great value to good people

231
00:11:45,320 --> 00:11:48,080
and whatever it takes,
I'm going to bring it home to them.

232
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:52,080
You have stolen so much from so many,
King Hydroflax,

233
00:11:52,240 --> 00:11:55,040
and I'm the woman
who's going to steal it all back!

234
00:11:55,280 --> 00:11:58,240
-What are you?
-I'm an archaeologist.

235
00:11:58,360 --> 00:12:00,560
Look, I've got a trowel.

236
00:12:03,920 --> 00:12:05,120
(LAUGHING)

237
00:12:05,560 --> 00:12:06,960
DOCTOR: Do not harm her!

238
00:12:07,280 --> 00:12:10,080
If you know what's good for you,
do not lay a finger on that woman.

239
00:12:10,280 --> 00:12:11,920
Ignore him! Attack!

240
00:12:16,040 --> 00:12:17,640
Garbage disposal, right?

241
00:12:17,720 --> 00:12:19,040
Get ready to say "Whee!"

242
00:12:19,120 --> 00:12:20,280
Put me down!

243
00:12:20,360 --> 00:12:21,760
DOCTOR: Back off from River Song.

244
00:12:21,840 --> 00:12:24,680
Give the order now.
Get yourself under control.

245
00:12:25,240 --> 00:12:26,920
Do not attack the female.

246
00:12:29,800 --> 00:12:31,760
Nobody move or the head gets it!

247
00:12:31,840 --> 00:12:33,640
-Do you really have a shooty trowel?
-It's sonic.

248
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:35,800
A sonic trowel. Do you realise
how ridiculous that sounds?

249
00:12:35,880 --> 00:12:38,920
-The threats are empty. Destroy them!
-BODY: Negative.

250
00:12:39,160 --> 00:12:41,400
78% chance of significant tissue damage.

251
00:12:41,480 --> 00:12:42,960
Do as you're told!

252
00:12:43,040 --> 00:12:45,960
Decision overruled.
Recommendation, chill.

253
00:12:46,040 --> 00:12:47,400
Look at that,
your body's got a mind of its own.

254
00:12:47,480 --> 00:12:49,880
More like an onboard computer
for the cybernetic component.

255
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:52,360
Plus inbuilt flash drive
and vernacular-friendly interface.

256
00:12:52,440 --> 00:12:54,480
-Cyber co-pilot.
-Mobile life support.

257
00:12:54,560 --> 00:12:56,280
-Sexy.
-It's not sexy.

258
00:12:56,360 --> 00:12:58,600
-It's a little bit sexy.
-Why is everything sexy now?

259
00:12:58,680 --> 00:12:59,960
Speaking of which...

260
00:13:00,040 --> 00:13:02,440
Ramone, prep for emergency extraction.
Two to go.

261
00:13:02,520 --> 00:13:04,680
-RAMONE: Standing by for teleport.
-Put it in the bag.

262
00:13:05,080 --> 00:13:06,720
-I'm sorry?
-The head. Put it in the bag.

263
00:13:06,800 --> 00:13:08,280
Do not put me in the bag!

264
00:13:08,520 --> 00:13:10,800
Quickly, do it!
Ramone, 20 seconds to jump.

265
00:13:10,880 --> 00:13:12,800
I will not be placed into a bag!

266
00:13:12,880 --> 00:13:15,000
Stop shouting a minute
if you want to go face-up.

267
00:13:15,080 --> 00:13:17,400
You will be crushed!
You will be destroyed!

268
00:13:17,720 --> 00:13:20,040
-You will beg my infinite mercy!
-Oh, zip it.

269
00:13:20,400 --> 00:13:22,800
Try to follow me
and I'll put him in a blender.

270
00:13:22,880 --> 00:13:24,080
Ramone, now!

271
00:13:28,320 --> 00:13:30,800
They will be tracked.
They will be found.

272
00:13:37,320 --> 00:13:39,280
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

273
00:13:39,360 --> 00:13:40,640
(GROANING)

274
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:44,120
Ramone! Just once
can you get the height right?

275
00:13:44,200 --> 00:13:46,160
RAMONE: Sorry, Professor.
HYDROFLAX: When I escape, I will bring

276
00:13:46,240 --> 00:13:48,240
-terror to you and your family!
-RIVER: Home in on my signal.

277
00:13:48,320 --> 00:13:50,400
-Have you located Damsel?
-RAMONE: I'm on it.

278
00:13:50,480 --> 00:13:52,160
The capsule is really close.

279
00:13:52,480 --> 00:13:54,600
-(DOCTOR LAUGHING)
-Is something funny?

280
00:13:54,680 --> 00:13:57,280
HYDROFLAX: Who dares laugh at Hydroflax?

281
00:13:57,360 --> 00:14:00,080
You shall be crushed!
You shall scream in fear!

282
00:14:00,440 --> 00:14:01,800
Let me out of this bag!

283
00:14:01,880 --> 00:14:03,640
RIVER: This is a serious mission
in a critical phase.

284
00:14:03,920 --> 00:14:05,880
There is nothing to laugh about here.

285
00:14:05,960 --> 00:14:07,520
We're being threatened by a bag!

286
00:14:07,760 --> 00:14:09,960
By a head in a bag!

287
00:14:10,040 --> 00:14:13,960
HYDROFLAX: I shall make dust of you.
My enemies are meat for the devouring.

288
00:14:14,120 --> 00:14:15,440
(BOTH LAUGHING)

289
00:14:16,440 --> 00:14:18,160
I can't approve of any of this,
you know,

290
00:14:18,240 --> 00:14:20,840
but I haven't laughed in a long time.

291
00:14:20,920 --> 00:14:23,120
-Well, good for you.
-HYDROFLAX: Prepare to die in agony

292
00:14:23,200 --> 00:14:25,560
and submit to my supremacy.

293
00:14:25,640 --> 00:14:27,280
Unzip this bag!

294
00:14:27,600 --> 00:14:29,720
(BOTH LAUGHING)

295
00:14:31,840 --> 00:14:33,120
You know, don't you?

296
00:14:33,200 --> 00:14:35,000
-Know what?
-Stop pretending.

297
00:14:35,080 --> 00:14:36,320
You know who I am.

298
00:14:38,080 --> 00:14:40,640
-Who are you?
-You know who I am. It's, it's,

299
00:14:40,960 --> 00:14:42,440
-it's me!
-Great!

300
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:44,720
Who are you?

301
00:14:45,040 --> 00:14:46,680
RAMONE: Professor Song!

302
00:14:48,840 --> 00:14:50,680
Sorry, Professor.
Sorry about the height thing.

303
00:14:50,760 --> 00:14:51,960
Prove it.

304
00:14:55,040 --> 00:14:57,520
(DOCTOR GROANING)

305
00:15:00,200 --> 00:15:01,760
Doesn't it get dull after a while?

306
00:15:02,480 --> 00:15:05,000
As an activity, it's not hugely varied,
is it?

307
00:15:05,880 --> 00:15:07,480
I'm so sorry.

308
00:15:08,000 --> 00:15:10,520
This is my husband Ramone.

309
00:15:10,600 --> 00:15:11,680
DOCTOR: Another one?

310
00:15:11,760 --> 00:15:13,800
-Are you going to kill him, too?
-We're not actually married.

311
00:15:13,920 --> 00:15:16,680
We are, in fact.
I wiped it from your memory.

312
00:15:16,800 --> 00:15:18,320
-Why?
-Well, you were being annoying.

313
00:15:18,560 --> 00:15:20,480
So the Damsel. Do we have a fix?

314
00:15:20,560 --> 00:15:22,400
Found the capsule
just over in the village

315
00:15:22,480 --> 00:15:23,840
but I can't locate Damsel.

316
00:15:24,000 --> 00:15:25,400
-I've looked everywhere.
-Who's Damsel?

317
00:15:25,480 --> 00:15:28,040
Have you been thorough? It's not easy,
you know, he does have 12 faces.

318
00:15:28,200 --> 00:15:29,920
RAMONE: None of these men are here.

319
00:15:30,320 --> 00:15:31,640
Are you sure it's one of these?

320
00:15:31,720 --> 00:15:33,760
RIVER: Yes, he only has these 12 faces.

321
00:15:34,280 --> 00:15:35,640
He'll be around here somewhere.

322
00:15:35,920 --> 00:15:38,640
This is the closest intersection
with the Doctor's timeline.

323
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:40,800
That's why I crashed
Hydroflax's ship here.

324
00:15:40,880 --> 00:15:44,200
-"Damsel"!
-Code name Damsel in Distress.

325
00:15:44,680 --> 00:15:46,400
Apparently, he needs a lot of rescuing.

326
00:15:46,480 --> 00:15:50,000
What if he has a face
that you don't know about yet?

327
00:15:50,080 --> 00:15:51,760
He has limits.

328
00:15:52,280 --> 00:15:54,080
Well, then. Let's go find him.

329
00:15:56,640 --> 00:15:59,080
BODY: You are in league
with the former queen?

330
00:15:59,520 --> 00:16:02,360
She employed me.
I didn't really know anything.

331
00:16:02,480 --> 00:16:05,240
-You have information.
-Oh, hardly anything, really.

332
00:16:05,480 --> 00:16:06,640
A tiny bit.

333
00:16:06,720 --> 00:16:08,360
You will give this information to us.

334
00:16:08,440 --> 00:16:10,640
Oh, absolutely. Of course I will.

335
00:16:10,720 --> 00:16:12,200
We will take the information.

336
00:16:12,280 --> 00:16:15,720
Ask anything you like.
I'll even write it down for you.

337
00:16:15,840 --> 00:16:17,120
That will not be necessary.

338
00:16:17,240 --> 00:16:18,360
You will be uploaded.

339
00:16:18,920 --> 00:16:20,720
We apologise for the inconvenience.

340
00:16:20,880 --> 00:16:22,120
Uploaded?

341
00:16:22,200 --> 00:16:24,120
-How?
-Recommendation,

342
00:16:26,240 --> 00:16:27,720
hold still.

343
00:16:27,800 --> 00:16:29,440
(WHIMPERING)

344
00:16:33,200 --> 00:16:35,120
No, this is no good.

345
00:16:35,400 --> 00:16:38,240
-I don't like this.
-Your cooperation is appreciated.

346
00:16:38,400 --> 00:16:39,760
I never agreed!

347
00:16:40,120 --> 00:16:41,800
No, this is unfair.

348
00:16:42,280 --> 00:16:44,200
Pursuit now commences.

349
00:16:44,320 --> 00:16:46,080
This is too tall!

350
00:16:46,160 --> 00:16:47,760
I'm afraid of heights!

351
00:16:48,280 --> 00:16:50,680
Recommendation, close your eyes.

352
00:16:52,040 --> 00:16:53,600
(WHIMPERING)

353
00:16:55,440 --> 00:16:57,680
(SCREAMING)

354
00:17:00,080 --> 00:17:01,480
RAMONE: What if we can't find him?

355
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:03,280
We need to get you off-world now.

356
00:17:03,360 --> 00:17:05,000
"Off-world"? People never say that.

357
00:17:05,080 --> 00:17:06,320
(LAUGHING) Are you new?

358
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:08,280
We can't hang around waiting.
He could be ages.

359
00:17:08,360 --> 00:17:10,400
Yes, he's probably off
rebuilding a civilisation

360
00:17:10,480 --> 00:17:12,480
or defeating giant robot fish...

361
00:17:12,560 --> 00:17:13,920
-We'll just have to steal it.
-Battling insects

362
00:17:14,000 --> 00:17:15,360
from the ninth dimension.
I'm sorry, what?

363
00:17:15,440 --> 00:17:18,400
The Hopper is really close. We'd be
out of here in less than ten minutes.

364
00:17:18,480 --> 00:17:21,120
I need time travel. I need this Tardis!

365
00:17:21,200 --> 00:17:23,080
I'm sorry, the word "steal”.
Somebody said "steal".

366
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:26,400
Yes, we are going to steal this box.

367
00:17:26,600 --> 00:17:28,160
Hush, you wouldn't understand.

368
00:17:28,240 --> 00:17:30,480
-You can't.
-Why can't I?

369
00:17:30,560 --> 00:17:32,760
-You can't just steal a Tar... A box!
-Why not?

370
00:17:33,560 --> 00:17:36,120
-Look, it says "Police".
-I have a key.

371
00:17:36,560 --> 00:17:37,600
Okay.

372
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:42,400
This Damsel person, he sounds...
He sounds pretty dangerous. Ish.

373
00:17:42,520 --> 00:17:44,960
It's a time machine.

374
00:17:45,480 --> 00:17:47,920
I can take it, do whatever I want
for as long as I like

375
00:17:48,000 --> 00:17:49,120
and pop it back a second later.

376
00:17:49,200 --> 00:17:50,800
-He'll never know it was gone.
-Yes, he will.

377
00:17:50,880 --> 00:17:51,920
How?

378
00:17:52,280 --> 00:17:54,200
-He'll just know.
-Well, he's never noticed before.

379
00:17:56,640 --> 00:17:59,560
Maybe he'll notice now.

380
00:18:00,560 --> 00:18:04,280
(LAUGHING) I'll see you on Temple Beach.

381
00:18:06,800 --> 00:18:08,800
I've already picked out your swimwear.

382
00:18:08,920 --> 00:18:10,080
RAMONE: Okay, but be careful.

383
00:18:10,200 --> 00:18:11,920
(SCOFFS) Absolutely not.

384
00:18:12,520 --> 00:18:13,800
You, with me.

385
00:18:13,960 --> 00:18:15,200
Bring the head.

386
00:18:16,480 --> 00:18:18,000
Please, look after her for me.

387
00:18:22,560 --> 00:18:23,600
Oh.

388
00:18:23,840 --> 00:18:26,280
Before you come in, you'd better
prepare yourself for a shock.

389
00:18:26,840 --> 00:18:29,800
It's not as snug as it looks.

390
00:18:36,480 --> 00:18:37,600
Finally.

391
00:18:38,720 --> 00:18:40,040
Finally?

392
00:18:40,480 --> 00:18:41,640
It's my go.

393
00:18:44,400 --> 00:18:48,880
Oh...my...God!

394
00:18:49,400 --> 00:18:51,240
(EXCLAIMS) It's bigger...

395
00:18:51,600 --> 00:18:53,360
-Uh, yes.
-...on the inside...

396
00:18:53,560 --> 00:18:54,800
-Look, we need to concentrate.
-...than it is...

397
00:18:54,960 --> 00:18:57,400
I know where you're going with this
but I need you to calm down.

398
00:18:57,480 --> 00:18:58,720
...on the outside?

399
00:18:58,920 --> 00:19:00,320
Well, you've certainly
grasped the essentials.

400
00:19:00,480 --> 00:19:03,320
My entire understanding
of physical space

401
00:19:03,400 --> 00:19:04,880
has been transformed!

402
00:19:05,000 --> 00:19:08,320
Three-dimensional Euclidean geometry
has been torn up,

403
00:19:08,440 --> 00:19:10,960
thrown in the air and snogged to death!

404
00:19:11,040 --> 00:19:14,240
My grasp of the universal constants

405
00:19:14,320 --> 00:19:18,120
of physical reality has been changed

406
00:19:20,200 --> 00:19:21,320
forever.

407
00:19:23,320 --> 00:19:26,360
Sorry. I've always wanted to
see that done properly.

408
00:19:26,600 --> 00:19:27,640
Would you like a drink?

409
00:19:28,040 --> 00:19:29,240
Aldebaran brandy.

410
00:19:29,520 --> 00:19:31,120
Help yourself. Don't tell Dad.

411
00:19:31,200 --> 00:19:33,200
-(BEEPING)
-What's that noise?

412
00:19:35,400 --> 00:19:37,760
It seems to have powered down.
Conserving batteries.

413
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:39,680
There's an inbuilt life-support system,

414
00:19:39,920 --> 00:19:41,960
-I'm not sure what powers it but...
-Really don't care.

415
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,680
-What's that noise?
-I don't know.

416
00:19:43,760 --> 00:19:45,240
-(BEEPING CONTINUES)
-Signal? Distress call?

417
00:19:45,320 --> 00:19:46,600
-Homing beacon.
-Possibly.

418
00:19:46,680 --> 00:19:47,720
So the rest of him is coming.

419
00:19:47,800 --> 00:19:49,440
Well, he must be very cross.
He's lost his head.

420
00:19:49,600 --> 00:19:51,360
Time we were off, then.

421
00:19:51,640 --> 00:19:53,320
(TARDIS SHUDDERING)

422
00:19:56,920 --> 00:19:58,400
You're doing it wrong.

423
00:19:58,640 --> 00:20:00,400
I am certainly not.

424
00:20:02,200 --> 00:20:03,680
Not those levers.

425
00:20:03,920 --> 00:20:05,200
Hush.

426
00:20:07,160 --> 00:20:08,880
You probably want to press that button.

427
00:20:08,960 --> 00:20:11,880
Why? That evacuates the waste tank
on deck seven.

428
00:20:12,200 --> 00:20:14,600
-Does it?
-What is wrong with you?

429
00:20:14,760 --> 00:20:15,960
Better avoid deck seven, then.

430
00:20:16,040 --> 00:20:17,440
Something's interfering
with the engines,

431
00:20:17,520 --> 00:20:19,600
which is technically not possible.

432
00:20:19,760 --> 00:20:21,760
-(CLEARS THROAT) Maybe.
-How would you know?

433
00:20:22,560 --> 00:20:24,560
Maybe the engines are
interfering with themselves.

434
00:20:24,680 --> 00:20:27,320
Wild theory, but what if this machine
had certain safeguards?

435
00:20:27,400 --> 00:20:29,560
For instance, maybe it can't take off

436
00:20:29,640 --> 00:20:33,520
when a life form registers as being both
inside and outside at the same time.

437
00:20:34,160 --> 00:20:35,360
Head and body.

438
00:20:36,240 --> 00:20:38,040
Which would mean, and again,

439
00:20:38,120 --> 00:20:40,880
I'm just wildly theorising here,

440
00:20:41,080 --> 00:20:44,120
that the door would not engage properly.

441
00:20:44,360 --> 00:20:45,600
Of course.

442
00:20:45,680 --> 00:20:47,600
It can't seal the real time envelope.

443
00:20:47,880 --> 00:20:50,520
Hence, it can't take off.

444
00:20:50,920 --> 00:20:54,200
Not when someone is in and out
at the same time.

445
00:20:54,320 --> 00:20:56,480
I mean, that just wouldn't be
good manners, would it?

446
00:20:56,560 --> 00:20:58,280
You're very quick.

447
00:20:58,360 --> 00:21:01,160
Yes. For a doctor.

448
00:21:01,720 --> 00:21:03,080
Yes.

449
00:21:04,440 --> 00:21:05,720
Seriously?

450
00:21:10,640 --> 00:21:12,040
NARDOLE: Hello!

451
00:21:12,120 --> 00:21:14,240
Hello. Is that you?

452
00:21:15,360 --> 00:21:16,880
Nardole, is that you?

453
00:21:16,960 --> 00:21:18,240
It's me, yes.

454
00:21:18,960 --> 00:21:20,280
Please.

455
00:21:20,400 --> 00:21:22,200
-You've got to help me.
-What's wrong?

456
00:21:22,400 --> 00:21:23,800
Where are you?

457
00:21:24,440 --> 00:21:25,760
In the alleyway.

458
00:21:26,160 --> 00:21:27,320
Can't you see me?

459
00:21:27,400 --> 00:21:28,760
Come a bit closer.

460
00:21:28,880 --> 00:21:29,960
What are you doing there?

461
00:21:30,080 --> 00:21:31,560
Help me!

462
00:21:32,000 --> 00:21:34,720
-Are you injured?
-Well, uh...

463
00:21:34,840 --> 00:21:36,400
Yes.

464
00:21:40,080 --> 00:21:42,040
Sorry! So sorry!

465
00:21:42,440 --> 00:21:44,040
-It made me.
-RAMONE: Nardole.

466
00:21:44,440 --> 00:21:46,400
Why are you pointing a gun
at your own head?

467
00:21:46,480 --> 00:21:47,640
It's not my head.

468
00:21:47,960 --> 00:21:49,200
Well, it is my head.

469
00:21:49,280 --> 00:21:50,320
But it's not my gun.

470
00:21:50,440 --> 00:21:52,000
-What happened to you?
-Please.

471
00:21:53,000 --> 00:21:54,920
Just do as it says.

472
00:21:56,000 --> 00:21:59,280
It's signalling. We have to assume
the body is homing in on this.

473
00:21:59,440 --> 00:22:00,720
-So how do we stop it?
-Well,

474
00:22:00,800 --> 00:22:03,720
-we could chop its head off. Oh, look.
-Does sarcasm help?

475
00:22:03,880 --> 00:22:05,240
Wouldn't it be a great universe
if it did?

476
00:22:05,360 --> 00:22:09,000
So summing it up, it's coming, we can't
take off, we can't seal the doors.

477
00:22:09,080 --> 00:22:10,440
-Yep.
-So...

478
00:22:11,240 --> 00:22:12,720
We just kill the head, right?

479
00:22:12,800 --> 00:22:14,880
-You can't shoot the head in the face!
-Why not?

480
00:22:15,520 --> 00:22:16,720
(SCREAMS)

481
00:22:18,120 --> 00:22:19,280
DOCTOR: Go on, then.

482
00:22:19,640 --> 00:22:20,720
Tell him to put his hands up.

483
00:22:20,800 --> 00:22:22,760
Do not fire if you value your lives.

484
00:22:22,840 --> 00:22:23,840
Why? What are you going to do?

485
00:22:24,000 --> 00:22:26,680
Kill me and my body will burn.

486
00:22:26,960 --> 00:22:30,040
-Burn what?
-This world!

487
00:22:30,120 --> 00:22:33,800
BODY: Enquiry. Are you acquainted
with the criminal River Song?

488
00:22:33,880 --> 00:22:35,360
That wasn't me. That was him.

489
00:22:35,600 --> 00:22:38,800
Repeat. Are you acquainted
with the criminal River Song?

490
00:22:38,920 --> 00:22:40,640
Please. Just answer it.

491
00:22:41,440 --> 00:22:42,480
Yes.

492
00:22:42,680 --> 00:22:45,040
You will take River Song a message.

493
00:22:46,080 --> 00:22:47,560
What message?

494
00:22:47,640 --> 00:22:49,520
RIVER: Suppose we believe you. How?

495
00:22:49,600 --> 00:22:52,360
My body contains
a split quantum actualiser.

496
00:22:52,520 --> 00:22:54,920
A perpetually stabilised black hole.
That's your power source?

497
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:56,280
What sort of medical school
did you go to?

498
00:22:56,360 --> 00:22:58,760
-A really good one for Doctors.
-More than a power source.

499
00:22:58,840 --> 00:23:00,520
If necessary, a bomb.

500
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,160
So you could wipe out
this solar system?

501
00:23:02,240 --> 00:23:04,280
-It wouldn't be the first.
-It would be your last.

502
00:23:04,360 --> 00:23:06,400
A fitting end
for the glory of Hydroflax.

503
00:23:06,480 --> 00:23:07,920
DOCTOR: So why haven't you
threatened this before?

504
00:23:08,000 --> 00:23:10,520
A king does not endanger his people
for no reason.

505
00:23:10,640 --> 00:23:11,840
You're endangering them now.

506
00:23:11,920 --> 00:23:13,360
-I'm cross.
-(POUNDING ON DOOR)

507
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:14,920
RAMONE: Dr Song, are you there?

508
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:18,520
-I have a message for you.
-Ramone! Get in here!

509
00:23:20,520 --> 00:23:21,720
(GASPS)

510
00:23:22,080 --> 00:23:23,600
You're going to die!

511
00:23:28,800 --> 00:23:30,080
(YELPS)

512
00:23:30,160 --> 00:23:31,520
-Kill her!
-No!

513
00:23:31,600 --> 00:23:33,480
-Put her down!
-Kill her now!

514
00:23:33,680 --> 00:23:35,920
-Death initiating.
-I'm so sorry.

515
00:23:39,560 --> 00:23:41,600
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

516
00:23:41,680 --> 00:23:43,440
-I'm sorry! No!
-(RIVER GRUNTING)

517
00:23:43,520 --> 00:23:45,280
Stop them! Stop them!

518
00:23:47,600 --> 00:23:49,280
-Where are we going?
-Get the head!

519
00:23:49,640 --> 00:23:51,160
-RAMONE: No!
-Stop them!

520
00:23:51,240 --> 00:23:52,280
BODY: Death initiating.

521
00:23:53,120 --> 00:23:56,080
-You set the coordinates. Where for?
-Just get the damn head!

522
00:23:56,680 --> 00:23:59,800
Kill them! Destroy them!

523
00:23:59,880 --> 00:24:01,320
(ALL SCREAMING)

524
00:24:02,440 --> 00:24:04,520
-Here!
-Kill them!

525
00:24:07,040 --> 00:24:08,360
With me!

526
00:24:09,200 --> 00:24:10,480
Where are we?

527
00:24:10,560 --> 00:24:12,320
-This way, come on.
-What about the box?

528
00:24:12,400 --> 00:24:13,960
Where are we going?
Stop holding my hand.

529
00:24:14,040 --> 00:24:15,880
-People don't do that to me.
-Hush now!

530
00:24:15,960 --> 00:24:17,880
And don't hush me.
I am not a hushing person.

531
00:24:19,320 --> 00:24:21,080
-(SOFT MUSIC PLAYING)
-(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

532
00:24:30,080 --> 00:24:33,800
FEMALE ANNOUNCER ON PA: We are
currently cruising at warp factor 12,

533
00:24:36,440 --> 00:24:40,240
traversing the fourth galaxy
of our seven-galaxy cruise.

534
00:24:41,000 --> 00:24:43,840
Next is the Andromeda Galaxy.

535
00:24:50,840 --> 00:24:54,000
Supernova approaching now to starboard.

536
00:24:57,640 --> 00:24:59,480
Ah, Dr Song!

537
00:24:59,680 --> 00:25:01,360
Your table is ready.

538
00:25:01,440 --> 00:25:02,800
Flemming!

539
00:25:03,040 --> 00:25:04,200
How are the twins?

540
00:25:04,440 --> 00:25:06,600
Still digesting their mother,
thank you for asking.

541
00:25:06,920 --> 00:25:08,320
I'm sure it was a lovely ceremony.

542
00:25:08,480 --> 00:25:09,800
FLEMMING: Oh, there were tears.

543
00:25:10,000 --> 00:25:11,560
And just a hint of screaming.

544
00:25:11,640 --> 00:25:13,360
(BOTH LAUGHING)

545
00:25:13,440 --> 00:25:16,040
Uh, Flemming, I wonder,

546
00:25:16,160 --> 00:25:19,320
could you deadlock seal
the baggage hold for me?

547
00:25:19,840 --> 00:25:22,920
It's a little irregular.
The other passengers might want access.

548
00:25:23,000 --> 00:25:25,520
Do you remember that time
I was transporting dragon eggs?

549
00:25:26,880 --> 00:25:28,200
Consider it done.

550
00:25:28,280 --> 00:25:29,280
(BEEPING)

551
00:25:29,720 --> 00:25:31,280
(DOORS LOCKING)

552
00:25:31,360 --> 00:25:33,920
-Is the gentleman here for dinner?
-Yes, he is.

553
00:25:34,000 --> 00:25:36,560
Excellent. I'll have the chef
prepare him immediately.

554
00:25:36,640 --> 00:25:37,680
DOCTOR: No, you won't.

555
00:25:37,880 --> 00:25:40,280
Uh, he will, in fact,
be joining me to eat.

556
00:25:40,440 --> 00:25:43,680
I was about to suggest that
force-feeding might be required.

557
00:25:43,800 --> 00:25:45,120
(BOTH LAUGHING)

558
00:25:45,240 --> 00:25:47,080
This way. Oh, may I take your bag?

559
00:25:47,320 --> 00:25:49,040
Oh, no, no, no. That's fine, thanks.

560
00:25:49,760 --> 00:25:52,240
(HYDROFLAX GRUMBLING INDISTINCTLY)

561
00:25:52,560 --> 00:25:53,720
Sorry.

562
00:25:53,920 --> 00:25:55,200
That was my stomach.

563
00:25:58,120 --> 00:25:59,640
I have an irritable bowel.

564
00:25:59,720 --> 00:26:01,560
HYDROFLAX: My revenge will be merciless.

565
00:26:01,640 --> 00:26:03,480
I will rip you open and devour you.

566
00:26:03,560 --> 00:26:04,840
It's having a day.

567
00:26:04,920 --> 00:26:06,480
HYDROFLAX: You cannot escape!

568
00:26:08,400 --> 00:26:09,480
This way.

569
00:26:09,560 --> 00:26:11,680
HYDROFLAX: Your actions
will not go unpunished.

570
00:26:12,360 --> 00:26:13,920
-Here.
-HYDROFLAX: Ow!

571
00:26:14,040 --> 00:26:15,960
I don't suppose you mind
if I freshen up?

572
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:20,120
Not bad for 200, eh?

573
00:26:21,320 --> 00:26:24,080
-2007?
-I have an augmented lifespan.

574
00:26:24,160 --> 00:26:26,040
-Long story.
-So what's the occasion?

575
00:26:26,240 --> 00:26:28,960
Ah, I've got the diamond.
Now it's time to sell it.

576
00:26:29,040 --> 00:26:30,680
I thought you were returning it
to the Halassi?

577
00:26:30,760 --> 00:26:33,840
(SCOFFS) Tell me. Were you born boring
or did you have to work at it?

578
00:26:34,040 --> 00:26:35,560
Where did you find a buyer?

579
00:26:35,640 --> 00:26:37,120
Look around you.

580
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:39,560
The Starship Harmony And Redemption.

581
00:26:39,640 --> 00:26:41,760
Minimum ticket price
one billion credits

582
00:26:41,840 --> 00:26:44,400
plus the provable murder
of multiple innocent life forms.

583
00:26:44,800 --> 00:26:47,360
Suites are reserved for planet-burners.

584
00:26:47,560 --> 00:26:48,680
Thank you.

585
00:26:49,000 --> 00:26:50,600
Even the staff are required to have

586
00:26:50,680 --> 00:26:53,480
a verifiable history
of indiscriminate slaughter.

587
00:26:53,840 --> 00:26:56,800
This is where genocide comes
to kick back and relax.

588
00:26:57,920 --> 00:26:59,040
Do try the fish.

589
00:27:00,880 --> 00:27:03,000
(POUNDING ON DOOR)

590
00:27:06,920 --> 00:27:09,880
Mr Flemming. There's an issue.

591
00:27:10,840 --> 00:27:13,280
- (CLASSICAL MUSIC PLAYING)
-(INDISTINCT CONVERSATIONS)

592
00:27:20,720 --> 00:27:22,120
Why are you frowning?

593
00:27:24,160 --> 00:27:26,440
-How did you know?
-It's audible.

594
00:27:27,040 --> 00:27:28,880
Deadlock seals can be broken.

595
00:27:29,360 --> 00:27:30,680
By geniuses.

596
00:27:31,000 --> 00:27:34,520
Hydroflax has a brain the size of a pea
and it's currently under the table.

597
00:27:36,080 --> 00:27:37,240
He's gone back to sleep, I think.

598
00:27:37,320 --> 00:27:38,360
You married him, though.

599
00:27:38,440 --> 00:27:39,880
I told you. I married the diamond.

600
00:27:40,120 --> 00:27:42,200
-How?
-I posed as his nurse.

601
00:27:42,280 --> 00:27:44,160
-Took me a week.
-To fall in love?

602
00:27:44,480 --> 00:27:47,480
(SCOFFS) It's the easiest lie
you can tell a man.

603
00:27:47,600 --> 00:27:50,760
They'll automatically believe
any story they're the hero of.

604
00:27:56,440 --> 00:27:57,760
River, there's, uh...

605
00:27:59,080 --> 00:28:01,360
There's something
I should probably tell you.

606
00:28:01,520 --> 00:28:02,520
WAITRESS: Dr Song,

607
00:28:03,040 --> 00:28:04,320
your guest has docked.

608
00:28:04,440 --> 00:28:05,960
He should be with you
in a very few minutes.

609
00:28:06,040 --> 00:28:07,840
Thank you. Whenever he's ready.

610
00:28:07,920 --> 00:28:08,920
WAITRESS: Of course.

611
00:28:09,480 --> 00:28:10,640
What's the book?

612
00:28:11,520 --> 00:28:13,320
Oh, it's my diary.

613
00:28:13,960 --> 00:28:15,880
One should always have
something sensational

614
00:28:16,080 --> 00:28:17,680
to read on a spaceship.

615
00:28:17,760 --> 00:28:18,760
Is it sad?

616
00:28:21,720 --> 00:28:23,080
Why would a diary be sad?

617
00:28:23,160 --> 00:28:24,440
I don't know. It's just that

618
00:28:25,560 --> 00:28:26,720
you look sad.

619
00:28:31,160 --> 00:28:32,160
It's nearly full.

620
00:28:33,000 --> 00:28:34,000
So?

621
00:28:34,160 --> 00:28:35,720
(RIVER SIGHING)

622
00:28:37,200 --> 00:28:38,560
The man who gave me this

623
00:28:39,080 --> 00:28:42,360
was the sort of man who'd
know exactly how long a diary

624
00:28:42,480 --> 00:28:44,240
you were going to need.

625
00:28:50,280 --> 00:28:51,760
He sounds awful.

626
00:28:51,840 --> 00:28:54,400
I suppose he is.
I've never really thought about it.

627
00:28:55,080 --> 00:28:57,040
Not somebody special, then?

628
00:29:00,680 --> 00:29:01,800
No.

629
00:29:03,520 --> 00:29:05,800
But terribly useful every now and then.

630
00:29:10,360 --> 00:29:12,720
Please, I just need you
to get me out of here.

631
00:29:12,920 --> 00:29:15,320
He's in the main hold, sir.
But you've deadlocked it.

632
00:29:15,480 --> 00:29:17,120
If you don't mind my observing, sir,

633
00:29:17,200 --> 00:29:19,920
you do seem a little nervous.
Is someone threatening you?

634
00:29:21,520 --> 00:29:23,360
-I'm the only one here.
-Confirmed, sir.

635
00:29:23,520 --> 00:29:24,920
There's only one reading in the hold.

636
00:29:25,760 --> 00:29:27,560
-I'm on my way.
-Be careful, sir.

637
00:29:28,000 --> 00:29:30,440
Don't worry. I'll just stick
my head round the door.

638
00:29:32,600 --> 00:29:34,240
DOCTOR: So who is this buyer?

639
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:37,080
RIVER: No idea.
He just responded to the advert.

640
00:29:42,680 --> 00:29:43,920
Which of you is Song?

641
00:29:44,280 --> 00:29:45,760
Who wants to know?

642
00:29:45,840 --> 00:29:48,200
-I am Scratch.
-Don't need your name.

643
00:29:48,280 --> 00:29:49,640
Are you empowered to purchase?

644
00:29:49,720 --> 00:29:52,120
I represent the shoal
of the Winter Harmony.

645
00:29:52,200 --> 00:29:53,440
Don't care, don't want to know.

646
00:29:53,520 --> 00:29:55,320
I'll need immediate payment.
Can you do that?

647
00:29:55,440 --> 00:29:59,040
And you could either just sit down
or fetch us the wine list or something?

648
00:30:04,640 --> 00:30:05,720
You have the diamond?

649
00:30:05,800 --> 00:30:08,120
Of course I have the diamond.
Show me the money.

650
00:30:25,640 --> 00:30:28,200
Just a thought, you probably
shouldn't do that in a restaurant.

651
00:30:43,760 --> 00:30:45,200
SCRATCH: Once instructed,

652
00:30:45,400 --> 00:30:48,640
this will transfer the necessary funds
to whatever account you choose.

653
00:30:48,720 --> 00:30:49,720
Thank you.

654
00:30:50,520 --> 00:30:51,520
The diamond.

655
00:30:51,840 --> 00:30:53,280
You're going to have
to dig for it a bit,

656
00:30:53,360 --> 00:30:56,360
but somehow I don't think
that's going to be a problem for you.

657
00:30:56,640 --> 00:30:58,240
-Is this a deception?
-No.

658
00:30:58,760 --> 00:31:00,080
The diamond is in there.

659
00:31:00,160 --> 00:31:02,280
This is a public place,
there won't be any tricks.

660
00:31:02,440 --> 00:31:04,760
This is not a public place.

661
00:31:13,520 --> 00:31:14,640
Block-booking. That's clever.

662
00:31:14,720 --> 00:31:16,840
You needn't have bothered.
I've brought what you want.

663
00:31:17,120 --> 00:31:19,480
Please do assume
that I have also taken precautions

664
00:31:19,560 --> 00:31:22,160
and don't do anything that might
make me cross and kill you.

665
00:31:22,360 --> 00:31:24,720
SCRATCH: Statement accepted.

666
00:31:24,800 --> 00:31:26,360
The diamond is here.

667
00:31:26,560 --> 00:31:28,120
(ALL HISSING)

668
00:31:29,400 --> 00:31:30,600
The payment, then.

669
00:31:32,280 --> 00:31:34,400
-(BEEPING)
-One hundred billion credits.

670
00:31:34,800 --> 00:31:38,680
As we agreed. This accesses
all the banks in the galaxy.

671
00:31:38,760 --> 00:31:39,960
Thank you.

672
00:31:40,200 --> 00:31:43,120
Here you go, then.
You may need to use a spoon

673
00:31:43,200 --> 00:31:46,040
-or knitting needle or something...
-Be it known,

674
00:31:46,440 --> 00:31:48,040
we do not do this for ourselves.

675
00:31:48,120 --> 00:31:50,600
-(SIGHING) I really don't care.
-We do it in honour

676
00:31:50,680 --> 00:31:52,720
of our distant and loving king,

677
00:31:53,280 --> 00:31:56,200
who once visited our world
in blood and joy.

678
00:31:56,400 --> 00:31:58,480
-Well, isn't that lovely.
-SCRATCH: We honour thee.

679
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:01,240
We prostrate ourselves in your name,

680
00:32:01,760 --> 00:32:04,320
-Hydroflax.
-ALL: (CHANTING) Hydroflax.

681
00:32:04,560 --> 00:32:07,440
For love of thee,
we do this thing today.

682
00:32:07,960 --> 00:32:10,360
-Hydroflax.
-(CHANTING CONTINUES)

683
00:32:16,400 --> 00:32:17,440
Give it.

684
00:32:17,880 --> 00:32:19,280
Give us the treasure.

685
00:32:19,680 --> 00:32:20,960
(CHANTING CONTINUES)

686
00:32:23,320 --> 00:32:25,120
What is wrong?

687
00:32:25,480 --> 00:32:27,120
Uh, well, uh...

688
00:32:27,600 --> 00:32:28,720
Awkward.

689
00:32:31,120 --> 00:32:32,440
I beg of you.

690
00:32:32,520 --> 00:32:34,800
-Not my head.
-Information is required.

691
00:32:34,880 --> 00:32:36,920
You know of River Song,
wife of Hydroflax?

692
00:32:37,960 --> 00:32:39,560
I... I do.

693
00:32:39,640 --> 00:32:41,720
I know River Song of old.

694
00:32:41,800 --> 00:32:44,800
And if you spare me,

695
00:32:44,880 --> 00:32:46,880
I'll tell you
who she's really married to.

696
00:32:46,960 --> 00:32:49,080
-Explain.
-You need a head.

697
00:32:49,880 --> 00:32:52,880
I can get you a head fit for a king.

698
00:32:53,400 --> 00:32:56,240
Why do you delay? We have paid.
We will receive.

699
00:32:57,440 --> 00:32:58,960
Yes, you will. (STAMMERING)

700
00:32:59,040 --> 00:33:02,360
By jingle, you will.
Yes, of course. But obviously

701
00:33:02,720 --> 00:33:04,760
we have to, you know, uh,

702
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:06,360
-check some...
-Things.

703
00:33:06,440 --> 00:33:09,600
...things. There are things that have
to be checked before I get it to you.

704
00:33:09,880 --> 00:33:11,320
If we don't check the thing,

705
00:33:11,400 --> 00:33:13,640
-then they...
-We will receive.

706
00:33:14,040 --> 00:33:15,320
Yes, you will receive,

707
00:33:15,440 --> 00:33:17,440
and here it is now.

708
00:33:17,960 --> 00:33:19,240
On its way...

709
00:33:19,320 --> 00:33:22,320
-(STAMMERING) This small...
-We will receive.

710
00:33:22,400 --> 00:33:23,480
Here you go.

711
00:33:23,560 --> 00:33:25,520
And you can...
You can have the bag as well.

712
00:33:25,640 --> 00:33:29,120
You know, it's been lovely

713
00:33:29,640 --> 00:33:32,840
but, uh, we don't want
to intrude on this special moment.

714
00:33:32,920 --> 00:33:36,320
So, why don't we just leave you
with the new baby?

715
00:33:36,400 --> 00:33:37,800
You will remain.

716
00:33:38,880 --> 00:33:40,440
Is that strictly necessary?

717
00:33:40,560 --> 00:33:43,600
I do not like surprises.

718
00:33:44,760 --> 00:33:45,800
Yeah.

719
00:33:46,160 --> 00:33:47,880
(SIGHING) Well, it's going to
be a funny old day.

720
00:33:50,920 --> 00:33:51,960
Oh, boy.

721
00:33:53,200 --> 00:33:56,000
You know what? I just can't stand
idly by and let this continue.

722
00:33:56,080 --> 00:33:58,800
-(HISSING)
-Death has been done this day!

723
00:34:00,080 --> 00:34:03,480
Noble blood has been spilled

724
00:34:03,560 --> 00:34:06,560
and our tears will surely follow.

725
00:34:06,640 --> 00:34:09,240
The sky shall crack.

726
00:34:09,480 --> 00:34:11,720
The ground shall heave.

727
00:34:12,800 --> 00:34:16,720
And even the rocks and the stones

728
00:34:16,800 --> 00:34:19,240
shall weep their rage.

729
00:34:19,560 --> 00:34:22,520
Behold the head

730
00:34:23,160 --> 00:34:24,640
of Hydroflax.

731
00:34:24,720 --> 00:34:26,080
(ALL HISSING)

732
00:34:27,880 --> 00:34:31,280
-(GLASS SHATTERING)
-Rest now, sweet prince.

733
00:34:32,400 --> 00:34:34,960
Walk amongst us nevermore.

734
00:34:36,760 --> 00:34:39,520
Shall we start the bidding
at 200 billion?

735
00:34:39,600 --> 00:34:40,920
I'm sorry, Professor Song,

736
00:34:41,000 --> 00:34:43,600
but we really couldn't keep
this treasure from the truly devout.

737
00:34:43,680 --> 00:34:46,640
Oh, my apologies to the truly devout.

738
00:34:46,720 --> 00:34:48,800
And shall we find out
who is the most truly devout?

739
00:34:48,880 --> 00:34:51,160
-This is heresy.
-Two hundred over there!

740
00:34:51,240 --> 00:34:53,000
Two hundred and fifty billion
by the sweet trolley!

741
00:34:53,280 --> 00:34:55,120
SCRATCH: Silence! This is not our way.

742
00:34:55,200 --> 00:34:56,880
DOCTOR: Well, it doesn't
say much for your king

743
00:34:56,960 --> 00:34:58,200
if you can't put a price on his head.

744
00:34:58,440 --> 00:35:00,400
Let's see what the king
himself has to say.

745
00:35:01,080 --> 00:35:02,840
(SCREAMING)

746
00:35:06,080 --> 00:35:07,120
Quick!

747
00:35:08,280 --> 00:35:09,440
Professor Song,

748
00:35:09,680 --> 00:35:11,320
has the food disappointed you?

749
00:35:11,720 --> 00:35:13,880
(ALL SCREAMING)

750
00:35:18,360 --> 00:35:21,280
At last. I am whole again.

751
00:35:23,520 --> 00:35:26,360
Come to me, my body!

752
00:35:34,640 --> 00:35:36,080
Well? Put me back.

753
00:35:36,320 --> 00:35:37,440
Scan in progress.

754
00:35:38,280 --> 00:35:40,600
You don't need to scan me,
just put me back.

755
00:35:41,320 --> 00:35:43,600
Tissue deterioration now irreversible.

756
00:35:44,800 --> 00:35:46,000
Well, what are you
going to do about that?

757
00:35:46,080 --> 00:35:49,400
Additional. The projectile inside
your brain continues to move.

758
00:35:49,640 --> 00:35:51,880
Prognosis, death in seven minutes.

759
00:35:51,960 --> 00:35:53,120
Well, I refuse.

760
00:35:53,480 --> 00:35:55,600
King Hydroflax does not accept death.

761
00:35:56,320 --> 00:35:57,840
Orders requested.

762
00:35:57,920 --> 00:36:00,640
Whatever I need to survive, do it now!

763
00:36:00,720 --> 00:36:03,600
Orders accepted. You need a new head.

764
00:36:03,680 --> 00:36:05,720
No, no,

765
00:36:06,600 --> 00:36:08,960
-not a new head.
-Orders implementing.

766
00:36:09,040 --> 00:36:11,480
No! No!

767
00:36:19,160 --> 00:36:21,760
I don't suppose you could fetch
that over for me, could you?

768
00:36:25,240 --> 00:36:27,040
As I was saying, Your Majesty...

769
00:36:27,840 --> 00:36:30,400
Well, Your Remaining Majesty.

770
00:36:31,320 --> 00:36:32,400
(GASPING)

771
00:36:33,440 --> 00:36:34,800
If it's a new head you're after,

772
00:36:34,880 --> 00:36:37,280
this is the guide to the very best.

773
00:36:37,360 --> 00:36:39,040
Don't touch that! Give that back to me.

774
00:36:39,120 --> 00:36:41,120
The diary of River Song.

775
00:36:41,280 --> 00:36:44,640
The ultimate guide
to the Time Lord known as the Doctor.

776
00:36:44,720 --> 00:36:46,240
Don't you dare touch that!

777
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:47,640
(RIVER GRUNTING)

778
00:36:47,720 --> 00:36:49,440
Long live the king.

779
00:36:51,680 --> 00:36:53,600
FLEMMING: "The Pandorica opens.”

780
00:36:53,880 --> 00:36:55,840
Ooh! That sounds exciting.

781
00:36:56,800 --> 00:36:59,080
And goodness me, a picnic at Asgard.

782
00:36:59,400 --> 00:37:01,880
Some people really know how to snack,
don't they?

783
00:37:02,200 --> 00:37:04,920
You should know, I have
a significant history of escaping.

784
00:37:05,400 --> 00:37:06,840
FLEMMING: "The crash of the Byzantium."

785
00:37:07,200 --> 00:37:08,760
Didn't they make a movie of that?

786
00:37:08,880 --> 00:37:11,280
-And when I do, I'm going to kill you.
-FLEMMING: Oh!

787
00:37:11,520 --> 00:37:15,440
"Jim the Fish." (LAUGHING)
Well, we all know Jim the Fish.

788
00:37:15,520 --> 00:37:19,280
And the longer you spend reading
my diary, the longer I'm going to take.

789
00:37:19,360 --> 00:37:22,120
And you've just been to Manhattan.

790
00:37:23,400 --> 00:37:27,320
-What planet is that?
-So do please keep going.

791
00:37:28,200 --> 00:37:29,480
This is irrelevant.

792
00:37:29,640 --> 00:37:31,720
If I may intrude, Your Majesty.

793
00:37:32,200 --> 00:37:35,600
The Doctor is a legendary
being of remarkable power

794
00:37:35,880 --> 00:37:37,920
and an infinite number of faces.

795
00:37:38,240 --> 00:37:40,400
His head, I assure you,

796
00:37:41,040 --> 00:37:42,800
-would be your crowning achievement.
-(KNOCKING ON ARMOUR)

797
00:37:43,000 --> 00:37:45,120
Besides which, uh,

798
00:37:45,320 --> 00:37:46,840
many of us on this ship

799
00:37:47,000 --> 00:37:51,280
would be happy to see his career
cut off, as it were, at the neck.

800
00:37:51,360 --> 00:37:53,720
Proceed faster
or your head will be taken.

801
00:37:53,800 --> 00:37:55,920
I would give my head with gladness.

802
00:37:56,800 --> 00:37:59,360
This woman is
the known consort of the Doctor.

803
00:37:59,480 --> 00:38:01,680
Confirmation required. Uploading.

804
00:38:05,200 --> 00:38:06,320
Ooh!

805
00:38:06,640 --> 00:38:07,640
Ooh!

806
00:38:07,720 --> 00:38:11,240
Is River Song the consort
of the Time Lord known as the Doctor?

807
00:38:11,320 --> 00:38:12,360
Huh?

808
00:38:12,880 --> 00:38:14,640
I think so, yeah.

809
00:38:14,720 --> 00:38:18,120
Here, can I stay up for a bit?
It's really very whiffy down there.

810
00:38:18,720 --> 00:38:20,280
Aw!

811
00:38:20,880 --> 00:38:23,320
-(MUFFLED) Aw, it's awful.
-So!

812
00:38:24,800 --> 00:38:26,080
Where is the Doctor now?

813
00:38:27,120 --> 00:38:29,680
I haven't the faintest idea.

814
00:38:29,760 --> 00:38:32,080
-Is that credible?
-It's true.

815
00:38:32,800 --> 00:38:34,880
FLEMMING: You're the woman he loves.
RIVER: No, I'm not.

816
00:38:35,040 --> 00:38:36,120
She's lying.

817
00:38:36,200 --> 00:38:39,440
RIVER: The Doctor does not
and has never loved me.

818
00:38:39,600 --> 00:38:40,640
I'm not lying.

819
00:38:43,520 --> 00:38:45,800
Confirmed. The life form is not lying.

820
00:38:46,000 --> 00:38:47,040
FLEMMING: Impossible.

821
00:38:47,120 --> 00:38:48,920
-This is a trick.
-RIVER: No, it isn't.

822
00:38:49,320 --> 00:38:51,680
My information is correct.

823
00:38:52,200 --> 00:38:55,600
-You are the woman who loves the Doctor.
-Yes, I am. I've never denied it.

824
00:38:56,240 --> 00:38:59,800
But who ever said he loved me back?
He's the Doctor.

825
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:03,040
He doesn't go around
falling in love with people.

826
00:39:03,120 --> 00:39:06,840
And if you think he's anything
that small or that ordinary,

827
00:39:06,920 --> 00:39:10,600
then you haven't the first idea
of what you're dealing with.

828
00:39:11,680 --> 00:39:14,880
Your Majesty, I assure you
she is the perfect bait.

829
00:39:15,080 --> 00:39:17,960
When this woman is in danger,
the Doctor will always come.

830
00:39:18,040 --> 00:39:20,320
Oh, you are a moron!

831
00:39:20,400 --> 00:39:21,480
No, he won't!

832
00:39:21,560 --> 00:39:23,840
-He's probably already here!
-No, he isn't. Of course he isn't.

833
00:39:23,920 --> 00:39:25,360
Possibly on this ship.

834
00:39:25,440 --> 00:39:27,200
RIVER: Well, go on. Scan it, then.

835
00:39:27,600 --> 00:39:29,280
-Go on, why don't you?
-River...

836
00:39:29,360 --> 00:39:31,240
Two hearts, stupid clothes,

837
00:39:31,320 --> 00:39:32,480
-you can't miss him.
-River...

838
00:39:32,560 --> 00:39:36,240
Go on! Scan the whole parsec.
He's not here.

839
00:39:36,560 --> 00:39:38,360
God knows where he is right now

840
00:39:38,440 --> 00:39:41,040
but I promise you,
he's doing whatever the hell he wants

841
00:39:41,120 --> 00:39:43,080
and not giving a damn about me!

842
00:39:43,160 --> 00:39:45,200
-And I'm just fine with that.
-River...

843
00:39:45,280 --> 00:39:48,440
When you love the Doctor,
it's like loving the stars themselves.

844
00:39:48,520 --> 00:39:51,360
You don't expect a sunset
to admire you back.

845
00:39:51,440 --> 00:39:53,480
And if I happen to
find myself in danger,

846
00:39:53,560 --> 00:39:56,640
let me tell you,
the Doctor is not stupid enough

847
00:39:56,720 --> 00:39:58,360
or sentimental enough

848
00:39:58,440 --> 00:40:00,920
and he is certainly not in love enough

849
00:40:01,000 --> 00:40:04,040
to find himself standing in it with me!

850
00:40:08,880 --> 00:40:10,120
(GASPS)

851
00:40:16,520 --> 00:40:18,160
(SOFTLY) Hello, sweetie.

852
00:40:24,400 --> 00:40:27,680
You are so doing those roots.

853
00:40:27,760 --> 00:40:29,840
-What, the roots of the sunset?
-Don't you dare.

854
00:40:29,920 --> 00:40:31,800
I'LL have to check with
the stars themselves.

855
00:40:31,880 --> 00:40:33,000
Oh, shut up.

856
00:40:33,080 --> 00:40:35,240
I was just keeping them
talking till it kicks off.

857
00:40:35,680 --> 00:40:37,040
What is this conversation? Explain.

858
00:40:37,120 --> 00:40:38,400
You keep out of this.

859
00:40:38,480 --> 00:40:40,600
-We need to get to work.
-Okay, what have you got?

860
00:40:40,680 --> 00:40:42,160
Four exits, two concealed,
one in the ceiling.

861
00:40:42,240 --> 00:40:44,240
-There's also one in the floor.
-No, I don't like it.

862
00:40:44,320 --> 00:40:46,160
-Too close to the engine ducts?
-Bit too tight.

863
00:40:46,240 --> 00:40:47,880
Oh, I hope you're not being personal.

864
00:40:47,960 --> 00:40:50,640
-Excuse me, what are you talking about?
-Hush! Mummy and Daddy are busy.

865
00:40:50,720 --> 00:40:54,040
-(CLOCK CHIMING)
-(GASPS) There we are. 2:00.

866
00:40:54,120 --> 00:40:56,760
-Here we go.
-Cease this conversation.

867
00:40:56,840 --> 00:40:59,520
Darling, in the event of a sudden meteor
strike on the lower starboard decks,

868
00:40:59,600 --> 00:41:01,440
where would you say
is the safest place to stand?

869
00:41:01,520 --> 00:41:03,400
-Meteor strike?
-Exactly here, I should think.

870
00:41:03,480 --> 00:41:05,600
Do you know what that isn't?
A coincidence.

871
00:41:05,680 --> 00:41:07,800
-Your escape plan.
-It's cheaper than a taxi.

872
00:41:07,880 --> 00:41:09,520
What meteor strike?

873
00:41:09,600 --> 00:41:12,200
FEMALE ANNOUNCER ON PA:
Alert. Meteor storm imminent.

874
00:41:12,840 --> 00:41:14,400
-That meteor strike.
-Alert.

875
00:41:14,480 --> 00:41:17,480
-How could you know?
-I'm an archaeologist from the future.

876
00:41:18,120 --> 00:41:19,600
I dug you up.

877
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,120
-Well...
-(RUMBLING)

878
00:41:23,080 --> 00:41:24,680
See you in 400 years!

879
00:41:25,000 --> 00:41:26,840
(ALL SHOUTING)

880
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,880
(ALL SCREAMING)

881
00:41:33,200 --> 00:41:36,440
I had this book,
History's Finest Exploding Restaurants.

882
00:41:36,520 --> 00:41:37,800
"The best food for free,

883
00:41:37,880 --> 00:41:39,440
-"skip the coffee.”
-What do you think, by the way?

884
00:41:39,520 --> 00:41:41,240
-Of what?
-The new body.

885
00:41:41,320 --> 00:41:43,680
I'll let you know.
I've only seen the face.

886
00:41:43,760 --> 00:41:46,320
How have you got a new one, by the way?
Aren't there rules?

887
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:49,080
-A thing happened.
-I bet it probably did. (LAUGHING)

888
00:41:49,200 --> 00:41:51,880
-Oh!
-ANNOUNCER: Starboard decks compromised.

889
00:41:53,000 --> 00:41:54,560
Please abandon ship.

890
00:41:54,640 --> 00:41:56,160
-(SIGHING)
-The diamond.

891
00:41:56,320 --> 00:41:57,360
Good, aren't I?

892
00:41:57,440 --> 00:41:58,960
-Please abandon ship.
-I'm not sure "good" is the word.

893
00:41:59,040 --> 00:42:00,280
Better not be.

894
00:42:01,760 --> 00:42:04,120
We need to get this ship stabilised.
Where's the bridge?

895
00:42:04,200 --> 00:42:05,840
-This way.
-Please abandon ship.

896
00:42:09,600 --> 00:42:11,040
(ROARING)

897
00:42:11,440 --> 00:42:13,120
We also need to stop that.

898
00:42:13,200 --> 00:42:14,360
Toss for it?

899
00:42:14,640 --> 00:42:17,080
-I'll take the robot. You drive.
-Okay.

900
00:42:17,160 --> 00:42:18,680
Oh, don't stop for strangers.

901
00:42:18,960 --> 00:42:20,240
Look who's talking.

902
00:42:21,000 --> 00:42:22,080
(SIGHS)

903
00:42:25,120 --> 00:42:28,120
-What's the point? It's over.
-I will take your head.

904
00:42:28,200 --> 00:42:29,200
What for?

905
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:32,320
We're on a crashing spaceship
and I don't even know if I can save it.

906
00:42:32,400 --> 00:42:35,160
You just shot your own king
in your own face.

907
00:42:35,240 --> 00:42:36,640
You'd get beheaded if you had one.

908
00:42:36,720 --> 00:42:39,080
I will take yours.
King Hydroflax will live again.

909
00:42:39,200 --> 00:42:41,320
(PEOPLE SCREAMING)

910
00:42:47,880 --> 00:42:48,960
Do you know what you need?

911
00:42:49,040 --> 00:42:51,160
You know what any decent
headless king needs?

912
00:42:51,240 --> 00:42:54,200
Money. This connects every bank

913
00:42:54,280 --> 00:42:58,320
to every other bank in this galaxy.
Right here, in my hand,

914
00:42:58,400 --> 00:43:00,160
all the money you can eat.

915
00:43:00,240 --> 00:43:01,400
Demonstrate.

916
00:43:02,920 --> 00:43:04,120
With pleasure.

917
00:43:05,640 --> 00:43:07,000
(BEEPING)

918
00:43:10,040 --> 00:43:13,360
Welcome to all the best firewalls
in the galaxy.

919
00:43:13,440 --> 00:43:15,640
Nothing is protected like money.

920
00:43:15,720 --> 00:43:18,760
Every stock market within a light year
is arguing in your head.

921
00:43:19,000 --> 00:43:20,560
I do not understand.

922
00:43:20,640 --> 00:43:22,680
(LAUGHING) That's the way
it is for most people.

923
00:43:22,760 --> 00:43:24,920
Do not understand. Do not understand.

924
00:43:27,800 --> 00:43:29,080
He had a bad day on the market.

925
00:43:29,160 --> 00:43:30,480
Do not understand.

926
00:43:31,120 --> 00:43:32,560
Do not understand.

927
00:43:32,720 --> 00:43:36,080
Sorry. I appreciate that wasn't really
funny but I couldn't help saying it.

928
00:43:36,160 --> 00:43:38,800
(BODY SPEAKING GIBBERISH)

929
00:43:38,880 --> 00:43:40,040
(SCREAMS)

930
00:43:41,320 --> 00:43:44,200
FEMALE ANNOUNCER:
Surface impact in two minutes.

931
00:43:45,000 --> 00:43:47,880
-Where's everyone else?
-They ran for it. So should we.

932
00:43:47,960 --> 00:43:49,520
We need to get the nav com back online

933
00:43:49,600 --> 00:43:51,800
-and reroute the thrusters.
-I'm trying.

934
00:43:51,880 --> 00:43:53,160
(BOTH EXCLAIMING)

935
00:43:53,280 --> 00:43:56,960
-So, King Hydroflax.
-Oh, how many times?

936
00:43:57,040 --> 00:43:59,440
-I married the diamond.
-So you say.

937
00:43:59,840 --> 00:44:01,200
-Elizabeth I.
-Ramone.

938
00:44:01,280 --> 00:44:03,240
-Marilyn Monroe.
-Stephen Fry.

939
00:44:03,520 --> 00:44:04,800
-Cleopatra!
-Same thing!

940
00:44:08,560 --> 00:44:09,840
Hang on a minute,

941
00:44:10,480 --> 00:44:11,920
I recognise that planet.

942
00:44:12,000 --> 00:44:14,600
Well, that's nice.
Maybe they'll name the crater after us.

943
00:44:17,040 --> 00:44:19,560
That's Darillium.

944
00:44:22,160 --> 00:44:23,320
Always good to know where we're going.

945
00:44:23,400 --> 00:44:24,560
Could you concentrate
on your work, please?

946
00:44:24,640 --> 00:44:27,160
You know, the Singing Towers?

947
00:44:27,240 --> 00:44:29,400
Yes, I'll be sure to give them a wave
as we zoom past.

948
00:44:29,480 --> 00:44:30,960
You always say
you're going to take me there for dinner

949
00:44:31,040 --> 00:44:32,840
and then you always cancel
at the last minute.

950
00:44:32,920 --> 00:44:35,120
I'd quite like to cancel this time, too,
if at all possible.

951
00:44:35,200 --> 00:44:36,600
(BOTH GROANING)

952
00:44:41,000 --> 00:44:43,560
What are you doing?
That's the internal teleport.

953
00:44:43,680 --> 00:44:47,280
(COUGHING) Yes, I can use the power cell
to boost the thrusters.

954
00:44:47,360 --> 00:44:48,880
Really? How?

955
00:44:49,120 --> 00:44:50,400
Hold these, quickly.

956
00:44:52,120 --> 00:44:54,480
-I don't see what good this will do.
-Sorry, River.

957
00:44:56,000 --> 00:44:57,840
Crashing spaceships, that's my job.

958
00:44:58,480 --> 00:44:59,640
(GASPS) You...

959
00:45:02,440 --> 00:45:03,680
No, you don't!

960
00:45:06,480 --> 00:45:07,520
(TARDIS WHOOSHING)

961
00:45:07,600 --> 00:45:10,640
More power. You can do it,
you can do it!

962
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:14,440
No, River! No, no. No, no, no!

963
00:45:14,520 --> 00:45:15,880
(WHOOSHING)

964
00:45:20,640 --> 00:45:22,240
Get back in the Tardis. This is my job.

965
00:45:22,320 --> 00:45:24,120
-This is my job!
-I've been doing it longer.

966
00:45:24,200 --> 00:45:25,560
-I do it better.
-River,

967
00:45:26,000 --> 00:45:28,640
not one person on this ship,
not one living thing, is worth you.

968
00:45:29,400 --> 00:45:30,440
Or you!

969
00:45:31,400 --> 00:45:35,000
FEMALE ANNOUNCER:
Surface impact in ten, nine, eight...

970
00:45:35,080 --> 00:45:36,240
RIVER: Teensy bit close.

971
00:45:36,320 --> 00:45:38,280
-Yeah, sort of.
-Darling, shall we pop back indoors?

972
00:45:38,360 --> 00:45:42,120
-Yeah, good idea.
-...four, three two, one...

973
00:45:43,080 --> 00:45:44,320
(BOTH PANTING)

974
00:46:06,800 --> 00:46:10,400
-(HEARTBEAT POUNDING)
-Indestructible as ever.

975
00:46:17,400 --> 00:46:19,080
"Married the diamond."

976
00:46:45,680 --> 00:46:46,720
(BEEPING)

977
00:46:48,840 --> 00:46:50,480
(WHOOSHING)

978
00:47:09,200 --> 00:47:10,320
ALPHONSE: Hello?

979
00:47:10,440 --> 00:47:12,560
Sir? (PANTING)

980
00:47:13,400 --> 00:47:16,840
-The ship, it came down. Did you see it?
-Yes, I did.

981
00:47:17,440 --> 00:47:20,400
-I've been searching for survivors...
-I doubt if you'd find any.

982
00:47:20,840 --> 00:47:24,000
And I don't think any of them
would be worth it, if that's a comfort.

983
00:47:24,240 --> 00:47:26,360
Brave of you to try, though. Well done.

984
00:47:27,600 --> 00:47:28,760
Thank you, sir.

985
00:47:32,680 --> 00:47:34,280
Those are the Singing Towers,
aren't they?

986
00:47:35,240 --> 00:47:37,400
Yes, sir. But it's just the wind.

987
00:47:37,480 --> 00:47:39,400
The Singing Towers of Darillium.

988
00:47:40,880 --> 00:47:42,920
Here we are at last.

989
00:47:43,000 --> 00:47:44,080
Sir?

990
00:47:45,560 --> 00:47:47,920
You know what? You should
build a restaurant right here,

991
00:47:48,000 --> 00:47:49,680
with a view of those towers.

992
00:47:49,760 --> 00:47:51,480
You'd make a lot of money that way.

993
00:47:51,560 --> 00:47:53,800
-You should do that.
-(CHUCKLING)

994
00:47:53,880 --> 00:47:55,760
You'd need a lot of money
to begin with, sir.

995
00:47:56,240 --> 00:47:57,920
The Halassi Androvar.

996
00:47:58,520 --> 00:48:02,080
I think you'll find that the reward
is pretty substantial.

997
00:48:08,240 --> 00:48:10,400
Why would you give me this, sir?

998
00:48:11,120 --> 00:48:12,560
(WHISPERING) Restaurant.

999
00:48:19,880 --> 00:48:21,360
(WHOOSHING)

1000
00:48:31,600 --> 00:48:32,640
Excuse me.

1001
00:48:32,880 --> 00:48:35,960
Um, I'd like a table on the balcony
with a view of the towers.

1002
00:48:36,040 --> 00:48:38,720
I'm sorry, sir. The first available slot
I have is Christmas Day,

1003
00:48:39,280 --> 00:48:41,480
-in four years' time.
-Not a problem.

1004
00:48:53,040 --> 00:48:56,320
Professor Song, the Doctor is
waiting for you on the balcony.

1005
00:48:57,760 --> 00:48:58,800
Oh!

1006
00:49:00,640 --> 00:49:02,720
-Excellent.
-This way, ma'am.

1007
00:49:03,760 --> 00:49:05,040
Do we have a good table?

1008
00:49:05,520 --> 00:49:07,560
WOMAN: The finest
in all the galaxy, ma'am.

1009
00:49:08,720 --> 00:49:10,520
Ah. Um...

1010
00:49:10,920 --> 00:49:11,960
One moment.

1011
00:49:20,240 --> 00:49:22,000
-Ramone?
-Professor Song.

1012
00:49:22,480 --> 00:49:24,280
The Doctor will be with you in a moment.

1013
00:49:25,080 --> 00:49:26,360
What are you doing here?

1014
00:49:26,520 --> 00:49:29,360
They pulled us from the wreckage, ma'am.
Fixed us up.

1015
00:49:29,800 --> 00:49:31,640
I've been working here ever since.

1016
00:49:32,560 --> 00:49:33,920
Don't worry,

1017
00:49:34,000 --> 00:49:37,120
the nasty part's all gone.
Got deleted in a merger.

1018
00:49:37,800 --> 00:49:39,000
What about Nardole?

1019
00:49:39,200 --> 00:49:40,680
NARDOLE: (MUFFLED)
Oh, Merry Christmas, ma'am.

1020
00:49:40,760 --> 00:49:42,120
Good to see you again.

1021
00:49:42,200 --> 00:49:44,640
(GASPS) Merry Christmas, Nardole!

1022
00:49:44,800 --> 00:49:47,760
Sorry I'm off duty,
I'm just having some "me" time.

1023
00:49:48,440 --> 00:49:51,520
I imagine that must
be quite a challenge.

1024
00:49:51,600 --> 00:49:53,520
NARDOLE: Yes, ma'am. (CHUCKLING)

1025
00:49:54,160 --> 00:49:55,840
So, Ramone.

1026
00:49:57,520 --> 00:49:59,720
-You have a metal body now.
-DOCTOR: Down, girl.

1027
00:50:03,800 --> 00:50:06,360
Now, that, my dear, is a suit.

1028
00:50:06,440 --> 00:50:07,720
Happy Christmas.

1029
00:50:08,760 --> 00:50:09,800
Really?

1030
00:50:10,880 --> 00:50:13,560
I don't think you've ever
given me a present before.

1031
00:50:18,400 --> 00:50:21,680
(GASPS) It's a sonic screwdriver!
How lovely.

1032
00:50:21,760 --> 00:50:24,000
When I saw the sonic trowel,
I thought it was just embarrassing.

1033
00:50:24,080 --> 00:50:26,120
-But look.
-(LAUGHING)

1034
00:50:27,840 --> 00:50:29,960
Oh, thank you.

1035
00:50:33,560 --> 00:50:35,720
You look, uh, amazing.

1036
00:50:35,800 --> 00:50:39,040
Oh, Doctor. You have no idea
whether I look amazing or not.

1037
00:50:39,120 --> 00:50:41,280
Well, you've moved your hair about,
haven't you?

1038
00:50:41,360 --> 00:50:43,720
Well done.
It's very sweet of you to try.

1039
00:50:44,400 --> 00:50:45,760
So what do you think?

1040
00:50:45,840 --> 00:50:49,200
(TOWERS SINGING ETHEREAL TUNE)

1041
00:50:49,880 --> 00:50:51,920
The Singing Towers.

1042
00:50:59,720 --> 00:51:01,200
(GASPS)

1043
00:51:06,880 --> 00:51:08,160
The music.

1044
00:51:09,480 --> 00:51:11,200
(TOWERS CONTINUE SINGING)

1045
00:51:19,200 --> 00:51:20,640
Listen to it.

1046
00:51:24,680 --> 00:51:26,240
Are you crying?

1047
00:51:27,360 --> 00:51:29,840
DOCTOR: No. Just the wind.

1048
00:51:30,880 --> 00:51:32,360
Nothing's ever just the wind.

1049
00:51:34,000 --> 00:51:35,560
No?

1050
00:51:36,400 --> 00:51:38,960
It blows through the cave system.

1051
00:51:39,040 --> 00:51:41,120
It harmonises with crystal layer.

1052
00:51:42,600 --> 00:51:43,840
Why are you sad?

1053
00:51:45,360 --> 00:51:46,520
Why are you sad?

1054
00:51:47,920 --> 00:51:50,440
I told you, my diary is nearly full.

1055
00:51:51,320 --> 00:51:52,360
I worry.

1056
00:51:53,240 --> 00:51:54,880
Please don't.

1057
00:52:00,040 --> 00:52:02,960
-There are stories about us, you know.
-Oh, I dread to think.

1058
00:52:03,040 --> 00:52:06,240
-I look them up sometimes.
-You really shouldn't do that.

1059
00:52:06,440 --> 00:52:09,440
Some of them suggest that

1060
00:52:10,880 --> 00:52:15,200
the very last night we spend together
is at the Singing Towers of Darillium.

1061
00:52:17,120 --> 00:52:19,520
That wouldn't be true, would it?

1062
00:52:22,440 --> 00:52:23,920
Spoilers.

1063
00:52:25,840 --> 00:52:27,240
(GASPS)

1064
00:52:27,800 --> 00:52:31,680
Well, that would explain why
you kept cancelling coming here.

1065
00:52:31,760 --> 00:52:34,280
-Remember when there were two of you?
-River, stop. Please stop.

1066
00:52:34,360 --> 00:52:36,520
Because I want you to know
that if this is the last night,

1067
00:52:36,600 --> 00:52:38,520
I expect you to find a way round it.

1068
00:52:38,600 --> 00:52:40,960
Not everything can be avoided.

1069
00:52:42,640 --> 00:52:43,680
Not forever.

1070
00:52:44,960 --> 00:52:46,200
But you're you.

1071
00:52:48,040 --> 00:52:49,280
There's always a loophole.

1072
00:52:49,400 --> 00:52:51,640
You wait until the last minute
and then you spring it on me.

1073
00:52:51,720 --> 00:52:53,040
Every night is
the last night for something.

1074
00:52:53,120 --> 00:52:55,240
-Every Christmas is last Christmas.
-But you will.

1075
00:52:55,840 --> 00:52:59,360
You'll wait until I've given up hope,
all will be lost

1076
00:52:59,440 --> 00:53:02,120
and you'll do that smug little smile
and then you'll save the day.

1077
00:53:02,200 --> 00:53:04,800
-You always do.
-No, I don't. Not always.

1078
00:53:07,240 --> 00:53:09,840
Times end, River. Because they have to.

1079
00:53:10,320 --> 00:53:12,360
Because there's no such thing
as happy ever after.

1080
00:53:12,560 --> 00:53:15,800
It's just a lie we tell ourselves
because the truth is so hard.

1081
00:53:16,840 --> 00:53:17,960
No, Doctor.

1082
00:53:19,520 --> 00:53:20,560
You're wrong.

1083
00:53:21,840 --> 00:53:24,240
Happy ever after doesn't mean forever.

1084
00:53:25,880 --> 00:53:27,960
It just means time.

1085
00:53:29,680 --> 00:53:31,520
A little time.

1086
00:53:34,720 --> 00:53:38,480
But that's not the sort of thing
you could ever understand, is it?

1087
00:53:40,160 --> 00:53:41,200
Mmm.

1088
00:53:43,440 --> 00:53:46,960
-What do you think of the towers?
-I love them.

1089
00:53:48,160 --> 00:53:50,200
Then, why are you ignoring them?

1090
00:53:50,280 --> 00:53:52,000
They're ignoring me.

1091
00:53:52,360 --> 00:53:54,040
But then,

1092
00:53:54,120 --> 00:53:56,760
you can't expect a monolith
to love you back.

1093
00:53:57,080 --> 00:53:59,080
No, you can't.

1094
00:54:01,440 --> 00:54:03,720
They've been there
for millions of years,

1095
00:54:03,800 --> 00:54:07,440
through storms and floods
and wars and time.

1096
00:54:08,520 --> 00:54:10,760
Nobody really understands
where the music comes from.

1097
00:54:10,880 --> 00:54:13,120
It's probably something to do
with the precise positions,

1098
00:54:13,200 --> 00:54:15,320
the distance between both towers.

1099
00:54:15,840 --> 00:54:19,000
Even the locals aren't sure.
All anyone will ever tell you is

1100
00:54:19,560 --> 00:54:22,360
that when the wind stands fair
and the night is perfect,

1101
00:54:23,600 --> 00:54:25,200
when you least expect it,

1102
00:54:26,840 --> 00:54:28,040
but always

1103
00:54:30,480 --> 00:54:32,400
when you need it the most,

1104
00:54:38,600 --> 00:54:39,960
there is a song.

1105
00:54:48,880 --> 00:54:50,200
So...

1106
00:54:51,880 --> 00:54:54,040
assuming tonight is all we have left...

1107
00:54:54,120 --> 00:54:57,400
-I didn't say that.
-...how long

1108
00:54:58,920 --> 00:55:01,120
is a night on Darillium?

1109
00:55:04,680 --> 00:55:05,960
Twenty-four years.

1110
00:55:07,360 --> 00:55:08,400
(GASPING)

1111
00:55:14,440 --> 00:55:15,880
I hate you.

1112
00:55:18,360 --> 00:55:19,520
No, you don't.

